imagery from multiple MODIS datasets which were combined and transformed
into two-dimensional matrices. We applied a gradient boosted machines model
to the lagged dataset values to forecast future values of the Enhanced Vegetation
Index (EVI). The predictive power of raw spectral data MODIS products were
compared across time periods and land use categories. Our models have
significantly more predictive power on held-out datasets than a baseline.
Though the tool was built to increase capacity to monitor vegetation health in
